adviseScripts.text: Ha!
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Hehe...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Why are you laughing?
Laugh with her.
Oh, nothing.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I just find it funny that a lowly Imposter like you is trying to give me advice.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Do you even know why I'm laughing?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I have a battle of wits with Noah.
Everyone from Eden just does whatever they want.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Harran acts like she's the only person in the whole world.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: And Isabel... she's got a few screws loose.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: What can I do to make myself even worse than them?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: What an oddball question.
Just keep doing what you're doing.
What? Why?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: It's a perfectly normal question.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Hm... so you mean to say that I'm already doing a good job?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: In your eyes, at least?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Excellent. I'll start with what I've got and turn it up a notch.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with Noah without any semblance of common sense.
Tell me, Imposter. How is a weakling like you even alive?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: You're nothing like a real Commander.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: A real Commander stands strong, even in the face of Raptures.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: It all comes down to having different equipment.
It's not necessarily the commander's duty to be strong.
Equipment is an important factor, yes.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: But let's be honest, isn't obtaining proper equipment a skill in its own right? Hee hee!
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Ugh, what are you even doing here?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Next time I'll ask the real Commander.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I have a back and forth repartee with Noah.
I don't understand the Ark.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: In Eden, we do not tolerate weakness in any form.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: But here, it's the complete opposite.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Why do the strong allow themselves to be held back by the inferior?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Why do they not simply leave them behind?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: The weak also have roles to play.
The strong have a duty to protect the weak.
Like selling clothes or making food?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Boring things like that, right?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: ... Duty?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I don't understand. It's not my duty to save others.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Noah is deep in thought.
The food in the Ark is simply grotesque.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Meat-flavored Splendamin instead of real meat.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Apple-flavored Splendamin instead of real apples.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Why is it like that? It's enough to make my stomach churn.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Because of food shortages.
Surprisingly, it's highly nutritious.
Well...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: You really should have seen that coming.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Did you really expect to live in a hole and still have anything to eat?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I see.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: That may be so...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: But, considering how foul it tastes, is it really worth it?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I talk with Noah about Splendamin.
Uh-oh! I'm in trouble.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Isabel found out I used to bully you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: So what?
Best of luck to you.
What do you mean 'so what'?!
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: We must fight to the death!
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Or, at least we'll fight until the real commander puts a stop to it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Ugh...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: This is driving me crazy.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I listen to Noah's concerns about human relationships.
I saw something new while I was walking down the road yesterday.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: What is an Ark Ranger?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: It's a hit show that plays inside the Ark.
It's a story of 5 masked heroes who vow to crush the Raptures.
A hit show? What is that?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Explain it in a way I can understand.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: What!?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text:
Not bad. Not bad.
Where can I see it?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I tell Noah all about the Ark Rangers.
Hey, Imposter.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I'm only asking because I'm curious, but...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Why do you take care of me even though I bully you all the time?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Cause I love... to hate you.
You're like a little sister to me. I can't hate you.
Hey, you're not actually upset, are you?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: A little sister?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Hmm...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Wait a minute...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Are you even older than me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: How can that be?! You're so puny!
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I have a heartfelt conversation with Noah.
I found one hell of a shield up on the surface!
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Hyyaaah!
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: What the heck are you doing?
Hey, that hurts.
Oh? What'd you say, you big bully?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Are you getting angry?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I'm not angry.
Hyyaaah!
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: *Smack*
How about now?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Still not angry.
Really? Impressive.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Pssh! Please.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I barely hit you...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: It's my heart that hurts.
I have nothing better to do, so I mess around with Noah.
When I went to visit the Outpost today,
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I saw something very fluffy.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Do you think I can touch it?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Are you talking about Poli?
Her name is Poli?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: ... I'll try and touch her next time.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: It was white! And small!
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: And fluffy!
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: It was making weird noises as it walked around, too.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I have a normal conversation with Noah.
*Swoosh* *Shhhwoosh* *Shhhwoosh*
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Noah is busy shadowboxing.
Oh... it's you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: If you think I'm actually gonna sit down and talk to you, you've got another thing coming.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: ... We can talk another day then.
Stand up to her.
Huh? Giving up so easily?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Aren't you supposed to be a Commander?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: The moment you encounter some resistance, you just give up! I can't believe it!
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: So you want to fight me, is that it? Well, take THIS!
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Noah lands a blow, and I start seeing stars.
I drop like a sack of potatoes.
Wait, what?! I knew you were weak, but I didn't actually think you'd...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: My session with Noah ended prematurely.
Tada~
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Noah hands me a small bottle.
Take a guess what this is.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Perfume?
Harran's perfume?
Nope.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Even though you got it wrong, I'll still give it to you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Wow, your intuition is on par with a Pilgrim.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Here. As your reward, it's yours.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Harran and I got into a little scuffle, and I swiped this from her.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I'm sure the owner will be coming to retrieve it shortly. Tata now!
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: After handing me Harran's perfume, Noah scurries away.
Let me ask you something.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Do you think there's a limit to how strong someone can get?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I don't think so.
I believe so.
My thoughts exactly.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: But a part of me finds all of this quite tiresome.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Since there's no limit, I can't have a moment's rest, no matter how strong I get.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: You moron, of course there's no such thing.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: If you defeat a formidable foe, a stronger one will come along and take its place. That is how it works.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Noah and I talk about the upper limits of strength.
I thought about it from every angle, and I have gotta say: I like my squad.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Can you guess why?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Because they're as strong as you are.
Because all of you work well together.
Good guess!
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: A strong shield can only work when paired with a spear that flies fair and true.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: You... what...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: How can someone... have such poor judgment?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: And to think you call yourself a Commander...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with Noah about the other members of the Inherit Squad.
When I was watching TV in your room today,
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: seeing a Nikke flying around with a skateboard.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: ... If I use my shield, do you think I can do the same?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: You can learn from her.
I will just get you a skateboard.
What? From her?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: You mean... the person on tv?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Wow, wait. You think she will really come?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Forget it... I don't want to carry around a burdensome thing like that on the surface.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I'd rather rip apart a Rapture and ride its pieces.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: You know that iron plate-looking thing attached to the exoskeleton? That round thing.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I do a plan with Noah about the skateboard.
You've got 10 seconds.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: You can order me to do anything, and I'll do it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: You have to meow at the end of every sentence.
Transform into your final form.
Oh, for crying out... can't you go a little easy on me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Is this really how a Commander should be behaving?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Whether I transform or not is of no importance.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I am a Pilgrim. I have always been whole.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: All right, your 10 seconds are up. Now it's my turn.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I go ahead and indulge Noah in playing a goofy game.
I really don't like those Pioneer guys.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: They're always going on about how they must protect humans, how everything is for mankind's benefit... blah, blah, blah...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: When have humans ever done anything for us?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: As long as you continue walking your own path, you'll be fine.
True belief is greater than petty things like personal gain.
Trust me, I was planning on it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: But, just so you know, I don't mean to say I've never received anything from you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Yeah yeah, but do beliefs put food on the table?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Seems like it's the opposite to me. Just look at Snow White, she's always going hungry.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Anyway, all I'm saying is that we should all learn to live on our own.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with Noah about Pilgrims who are on different paths.
Hey. Hellooooo...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Have you ever dozed off during a battle?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: How is that even possible?
You mean you have before?
Sure it is. Just because you haven't experienced it yourself doesn't mean it's not possible.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: For example...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: A throng of enemies appears. I deploy my shield, and I take a cat nap for a few minutes. The end.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: That's all there is to it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Do I have to spell it out for you?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Once you get as strong as I have,
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: you can decimate your enemies even while you're asleep.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I listen patiently as Noah bragged about her prowess in battle.
You see these horns on my head?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: All of our squad members have them.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Guess what we use them for. If you get it right, I won't bug you anymore today.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: They're used as a high-tech communication device.
They're just for decoration.
What?! How did you know?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: You're not some kind of spy, are you?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: ... Ahem... Anyway, there's more to it than that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: What?!
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I mean, sure... they may look nice...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: but they're meant to serve another purpose, which is...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I listen as Noah unveiled the secret purpose of the Inherit Squad members' horns.
Your body is so fragile compared to a Nikke's.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Have you ever thought about swapping it for a mechanical body?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I want to become strong while remaining a human.
I'm not opposed to the idea.
Huh? So to you, if your body is mechanical, that means you're no longer human?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Then the real Commander is a monst...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: ... Oh. That actually makes sense.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Wow. For such a puny little creature, you certainly are determined.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Very good. Well then, shall we head up to the surface and gather some parts?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Wait for a second...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: Now that I think about it... If you get stronger, then I wouldn't be able to keep making fun of you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noah

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with Noah about strengthening the body.
